text: Michaela Španková (born 1 August 1999) is a Slovak female volleyball player. She is part of the Slovakia women's national volleyball team. She competed at the 2019 Women's European Volleyball Championship. ==Clubs== * VKM Piešťany (2010–2014) * COP NITRA (2014–2016) * Volley project UKF Nitra (2016–2018) * Strabag VC FTVŠ UK Bratislava (2018–2019) == References == == External links == * Profile on CEV Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Slovak women's volleyball players Category:Sportspeople from Liptovský Mikuláš
